    • Fraction

      public Fraction(BigInteger numerator, BigInteger denominator)
      Translate a BigInteger numerator and denominator to its Fraction representation. If denominator is negative, both numerator and denominator are negated to prevent a negative denominator. Fraction is always reduced to the simplest form.
      Parameters:
      numerator - BigInteger representation of the numerator
      denominator - BigInteger representation of the denominator
      Throws:
      ArithmeticException - if denominator equals ZERO
      See Also:
      • BigInteger

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Fraction other)
      Compares this Fraction with the specified other Fraction. This method is provided in preference to individual methods for each of the six boolean comparison operators (<, ==, >, >=, !=, <=). The suggested idiom for performing these comparisons is: (x.compareTo(y) <op> 0), where <op> is one of the six comparison operators.
      Parameters:
      other - Fraction to which this Fraction is to be compared.
      Returns:
      -1, 0 or 1 as this Fraction is numerically less than, equal to, or greater than other Fraction.

    • min

      public Fraction min(Fraction other)
      Returns the minimum of this Fraction and other Fraction.
      Parameters:
      other - value with which the minimum is to be computed.
      Returns:
      the Fraction whose value is the lesser of this Fraction and other Fraction. If they are equal, this Fraction is returned.
